main event: Two irregular objects were picked up on ground radar southwest of Stuttgart, Germany on January 3, 1961.
interesting points: A round-shaped object appeared on radar, then disappeared.
Another object was then detected on radar, which reached a zenith and then dived out after passage.
The objects moved faster than anything the witnesses had ever seen before.
The sighting was considered a valid indication of the presence of Unidentified Flying Objects.
The objects exhibited unusual capabilities in their movements, color, and size.
sighted object: Two irregular objects detected on ground radar
